H1: nofill Filter

H2: Interface

!filter_interface "nofill"

H2: Description

The {{nofill}} filter is used to format a set of lines, i.e.
lines are separated by newline characters.

Note: The {{FILT:address}} filter
may be a better choice that nofill in certain cases.
Unlike nofill, address is mapped to ADDRESS tags when
HTML is generated. (It's then up to the browser to decide
how the address is formatted.)

H2: Examples

!block example; lang='sdf'
!block nofill
Mr I.M. Lucky
B.Sc. (Computing)
B.Fun. (Eating)
!endblock
!endblock

The output is:

!block nofill
Mr I.M. Lucky
B.Sc. (Computing)
B.Fun. (Eating)
!endblock

